#!   MARKDOWN_DESCRIPTION="**Description** &#10;&#10;This workbench read and trasform all the metadata for the provinces of Manitoba (MB) and Saskatchewan (SK).&#10;&#10;&#10;**Input Ports** &#10;&#10;- None&#10;&#10;&#10;**Output Ports** &#10;&#10;- None&#10;&#10;**Parameters** &#10;&#10;  - ACTIVATE_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the geospatial features; No: Do not process the geospatial features.&#10;&#10;  - ACTIVATE_NON_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the none geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the none geospatial features; No: Do not process the none geospatial features.&#10;&#10;  - ACTIVATE_TRANSLATION: Flag enabling the translation of the texts using AWS service. Can take two values: Yes: Translates the texts; No: Do not translate the texts.  The Yes flag can only be used in production mode.&#10;&#10;  - DCAT_READER_SELECT: Flag enabling the reading of the metadata from the P/T web service. Can take two values: Yes: Read the metadata from the P/T web service; No: Read the metadata from a local source on disk.&#10;&#10;  - FORCED_PYCSW_URL: URL address of the PYCSW server used to update the metadata.&#10;&#10;  - IN_FFS_TESTING_FILE: Name of a FFS file containing the metadata records read from the DCAT_READER. This file is used when the parameter: _DCAT_READER_SELECT_ is set to _No_.&#10;&#10; - LOCAL_SOURCE_METADATA_DELTA_FINDER: Flag enabling the use of a local source for the metadata delta finder. Can take two values: Yes: Use a local source as defined by the parameter OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: use the content PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCED_PYCSW_URL.&#10;&#10; - LOCAL_WRITER: Flag enabling to write the output locally or on the server.  Can take two values: Yes: Write the output locally as defined by the parameter:OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: Write the output in the PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCEDS_PYCSW_URL.&#10;&#10; - P-T_ABBR: Two or three letter abbreviation code of the province or terrirtory (ex.: ON, QC, PEI, ...).&#10;&#10; - METADATA_OVERWRITE: Enable the overwite of the PyCSW.  Can take two values: Yes: Overwrite the contentof the PyCSW; No: Do no overwrite the content of the PyCSW.&#10;&#10;  - IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR: Root working directory defined by default as: _(FME_SHAREDRESOURCE_DATA)_\ _PT_Harvester_.  Used to define the following _private parameters_:&#10;&#10;    - IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Source directory of the root of the lookup table files. Defined as: (IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR)\ _LOOKUP_TABLES_&#10;&#10;    - IN_GMD_XML_TEMPLATE_DIR: Source directory of the root XML templates. Defined as: (IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR)\ _XML_TEMPLATES_&#10;&#10;    - IN_TBS_JSON_TEMPLATE_DIR: Source directory of the root JSON templates. Defined as: (IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR)\ _JSON_TEMPLATES_&#10;&#10;    - LOG_FILE: Output log file. Defined as: (IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR)\ (P-T_ABBR)\ _LOG_\ (P-T_ABBR)_.log_&#10;&#10;    - OUT_JSON_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output JSON files. Defined as: (IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR)\ (P-T_ABBR)\ _JSON_LOCAL_&#10;&#10;    - OUT_XLS_NOTIFICATION_DIR: Source directory to output excel files. Defined as: (IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR)\ (P-T_ABBR)\ _XLS_&#10;&#10;    - OUT_XML_FAILED_DIR: Source directory to output failed XML files. Defined as: (IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR)\ (P-T_ABBR)\ _XML_FAILED_&#10;&#10;    - OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output _Local Source_ XML files. Defined as: (IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR)\ (P-T_ABBR)\ _XML_LOCAL_&#10;&#10;    - OUT_XML_PASSED_DIR: Source directory to output passedXML files. Defined as: (IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR)\ (P-T_ABBR)\ _XML_PASSED_&#10;&#10; - URL_VALIDATION : Indicates to validate or not created URL. (Should be Yes for prod)&#10;"
#!   MARKDOWN_USAGE=""
